724956f-a.text:
End Street, at and adjoining the Northeast Corner of 27th Ave. (foreground), showing in the foreground the Wade house. Beyond it was the home of Benjamin S.H. Maillefert from 1867-1882. Here Elinabeth
his daughter married Fred Mackill.
1922.
Eumene L. Ambruster Collection.

724958f-d.text:
2nd Street, east side, between 27th and Astoria Avenuen, showing the Judge Munson House, a stone structure built in 1840 by Stephen A. Halsey. It was occupied by Captain Munson in 1866. From 1889 to 1896 the house was the Long Island City High School and later became Public School No. 9. E. L. Armbruster is authority for the above data. Views 1,2: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  1923
View 3: George D. -hinn  April, 1940
View 4: P.L.Sperr  March 13, 1931
